text.tspan: - The pins on the RP2040 can be muxed! For more
information on the multiplexed pins, check out "section
1.4.3 GPIO Functions" of the RP2040 datasheet.
- GPIO## refers to the RP2040 pins on the IC while the
G## refers to the pins based on the MicroMod
nomenclature. To control the pin based on your
programming language, make sure to reference the
ROM: 16kB (fixed at time of silicon is manufactured)
USB: 5V at ~500mA (default), dependent on USB Port
